{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":915,"text":"It's very nice to be here tonight."}]},{"cues":[{"time":2880,"text":"So I've been working on the history of income"},{"time":6596,"text":"and wealth distribution for the past 15 years,"},{"time":9915,"text":"and one of the interesting lessons"},{"time":13016,"text":"coming from this historical evidence"},{"time":15517,"text":"is indeed that, in the long run,"},{"time":17530,"text":"there is a tendency for \nthe rate of return of capital"},{"time":21250,"text":"to exceed the economy's growth rate,"},{"time":23920,"text":"and this tends to lead to \nhigh concentration of wealth."},{"time":26665,"text":"Not infinite concentration of wealth,"},{"time":28498,"text":"but the higher the gap between r and g,"},{"time":31289,"text":"the higher the level of inequality of wealth"},{"time":34224,"text":"towards which society tends to converge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37431,"text":"So this is a key force that\nI'm going to talk about today,"},{"time":40985,"text":"but let me say right away"},{"time":42954,"text":"that this is not the only important force"},{"time":45284,"text":"in the dynamics of income \nand wealth distribution,"},{"time":47757,"text":"and there are many other forces that play"},{"time":49782,"text":"an important role in the long-run dynamics"},{"time":52763,"text":"of income and wealth distribution."},{"time":54338,"text":"Also there is a lot of data"},{"time":56307,"text":"that still needs to be collected."},{"time":57863,"text":"We know a little bit more today"},{"time":60795,"text":"than we used to know, \nbut we still know too little,"},{"time":63316,"text":"and certainly there are \nmany different processes —"},{"time":65992,"text":"economic, social, political —"},{"time":68290,"text":"that need to be studied more."},{"time":69717,"text":"And so I'm going to focus today on this simple force,"},{"time":72697,"text":"but that doesn't mean that other important forces"},{"time":74958,"text":"do not exist."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76162,"text":"So most of the data I'm going to present"},{"time":78434,"text":"comes from this database"},{"time":80639,"text":"that's available online:"},{"time":81899,"text":"the World Top Incomes Database."},{"time":83384,"text":"So this is the largest existing"},{"time":85487,"text":"historical database on inequality,"},{"time":87940,"text":"and this comes from the effort"},{"time":89290,"text":"of over 30 scholars from several dozen countries."},{"time":93182,"text":"So let me show you a couple of facts"},{"time":95960,"text":"coming from this database,"},{"time":97105,"text":"and then we'll return to r bigger than g."},{"time":99179,"text":"So fact number one is that there has been"},{"time":101689,"text":"a big reversal in the ordering of income inequality"},{"time":104740,"text":"between the United States and Europe"},{"time":106645,"text":"over the past century."},{"time":108400,"text":"So back in 1900, 1910, income inequality was actually"},{"time":111905,"text":"much higher in Europe than in the United States,"},{"time":114170,"text":"whereas today, it is a lot higher in the United States."},{"time":117280,"text":"So let me be very clear:"},{"time":118946,"text":"The main explanation for this is not r bigger than g."},{"time":121770,"text":"It has more to do with changing supply and demand"},{"time":125267,"text":"for skill, the race between education and technology,"},{"time":128720,"text":"globalization, probably more unequal access"},{"time":132300,"text":"to skills in the U.S.,"},{"time":133906,"text":"where you have very good, very top universities"},{"time":136493,"text":"but where the bottom part of the educational system"},{"time":138735,"text":"is not as good,"},{"time":139500,"text":"so very unequal access to skills,"},{"time":141861,"text":"and also an unprecedented rise"},{"time":143780,"text":"of top managerial compensation of the United States,"},{"time":146800,"text":"which is difficult to account for\njust on the basis of education."},{"time":149650,"text":"So there is more going on here,"},{"time":151604,"text":"but I'm not going to talk too much about this today,"},{"time":154213,"text":"because I want to focus on wealth inequality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156879,"text":"So let me just show you a very simple indicator"},{"time":159860,"text":"about the income inequality part."},{"time":162210,"text":"So this is the share of total income"},{"time":164664,"text":"going to the top 10 percent."},{"time":166452,"text":"So you can see that one century ago,"},{"time":168624,"text":"it was between 45 and 50 percent in Europe"},{"time":172201,"text":"and a little bit above 40 percent in the U.S.,"},{"time":174939,"text":"so there was more inequality in Europe."},{"time":177210,"text":"Then there was a sharp decline"},{"time":179234,"text":"during the first half of the 20th century,"},{"time":181765,"text":"and in the recent decade, you can see that"},{"time":184128,"text":"the U.S. has become more unequal than Europe,"},{"time":187630,"text":"and this is the first fact I just talked about."},{"time":190300,"text":"Now, the second fact is more about wealth inequality,"},{"time":194211,"text":"and here the central fact is that wealth inequality"},{"time":197301,"text":"is always a lot higher than income inequality,"},{"time":199907,"text":"and also that wealth inequality,"},{"time":202292,"text":"although it has also increased in recent decades,"},{"time":204945,"text":"is still less extreme today"},{"time":206801,"text":"than what it was a century ago,"},{"time":208680,"text":"although the total quantity of wealth"},{"time":211199,"text":"relative to income has now recovered"},{"time":213224,"text":"from the very large shocks"},{"time":214855,"text":"caused by World War I, the Great Depression,"},{"time":216880,"text":"World War II."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218099,"text":"So let me show you two graphs"},{"time":220143,"text":"illustrating fact number two and fact number three."},{"time":223000,"text":"So first, if you look at the level of wealth inequality,"},{"time":227390,"text":"this is the share of total wealth"},{"time":230548,"text":"going to the top 10 percent of wealth holders,"},{"time":233070,"text":"so you can see the same kind of reversal"},{"time":235779,"text":"between the U.S. and Europe that we had before"},{"time":238344,"text":"for income inequality."},{"time":240020,"text":"So wealth concentration was higher"},{"time":243570,"text":"in Europe than in the U.S. a century ago,"},{"time":245813,"text":"and now it is the opposite."},{"time":247647,"text":"But you can also show two things:"},{"time":249638,"text":"First, the general level of wealth inequality"},{"time":253339,"text":"is always higher than income inequality."},{"time":255994,"text":"So remember, for income inequality,"},{"time":258334,"text":"the share going to the top 10 percent"},{"time":260662,"text":"was between 30 and 50 percent of total income,"},{"time":264960,"text":"whereas for wealth, the share is always"},{"time":267772,"text":"between 60 and 90 percent."},{"time":269831,"text":"Okay, so that's fact number one,"},{"time":271347,"text":"and that's very important for what follows."},{"time":273273,"text":"Wealth concentration is always"},{"time":274994,"text":"a lot higher than income concentration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276873,"text":"Fact number two is that the rise"},{"time":280259,"text":"in wealth inequality in recent decades"},{"time":283206,"text":"is still not enough to get us back to 1910."},{"time":287492,"text":"So the big difference today,"},{"time":289269,"text":"wealth inequality is still very large,"},{"time":291182,"text":"with 60, 70 percent of total wealth for the top 10,"},{"time":294444,"text":"but the good news is that it's actually"},{"time":296289,"text":"better than one century ago,"},{"time":298070,"text":"where you had 90 percent in\nEurope going to the top 10."},{"time":301441,"text":"So today what you have"},{"time":303432,"text":"is what I call the middle 40 percent,"},{"time":305434,"text":"the people who are not in the top 10"},{"time":307347,"text":"and who are not in the bottom 50,"},{"time":309120,"text":"and what you can view as the wealth middle class"},{"time":311386,"text":"that owns 20 to 30 percent"},{"time":314529,"text":"of total wealth, national wealth,"},{"time":316391,"text":"whereas they used to be poor, a century ago,"},{"time":319722,"text":"when there was basically no wealth middle class."},{"time":322340,"text":"So this is an important change,"},{"time":323917,"text":"and it's interesting to see that wealth inequality"},{"time":328532,"text":"has not fully recovered to pre-World War I levels,"},{"time":331838,"text":"although the total quantity of wealth has recovered."},{"time":335347,"text":"Okay? So this is the total value"},{"time":337294,"text":"of wealth relative to income,"},{"time":339510,"text":"and you can see that in particular in Europe,"},{"time":341623,"text":"we are almost back to the pre-World War I level."},{"time":345483,"text":"So there are really two"},{"time":347328,"text":"different parts of the story here."},{"time":349859,"text":"One has to do with"},{"time":350978,"text":"the total quantity of wealth that we accumulate,"},{"time":353420,"text":"and there is nothing bad per se, of course,"},{"time":355098,"text":"in accumulating a lot of wealth,"},{"time":356845,"text":"and in particular if it is more diffuse"},{"time":359713,"text":"and less concentrated."},{"time":361107,"text":"So what we really want to focus on"},{"time":363852,"text":"is the long-run evolution of wealth inequality,"},{"time":366233,"text":"and what's going to happen in the future."},{"time":368533,"text":"How can we account for the fact that"},{"time":370558,"text":"until World War I, wealth inequality was so high"},{"time":374220,"text":"and, if anything, was rising to even higher levels,"},{"time":377410,"text":"and how can we think about the future?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":380737,"text":"So let me come to some of the explanations"},{"time":384623,"text":"and speculations about the future."},{"time":386759,"text":"Let me first say that"},{"time":388354,"text":"probably the best model to explain"},{"time":390341,"text":"why wealth is so much"},{"time":392438,"text":"more concentrated than income"},{"time":394624,"text":"is a dynamic, dynastic model"},{"time":397736,"text":"where individuals have a long horizon"},{"time":400200,"text":"and accumulate wealth for all sorts of reasons."},{"time":402956,"text":"If people were accumulating wealth"},{"time":405566,"text":"only for life cycle reasons,"},{"time":407569,"text":"you know, to be able to consume"},{"time":409582,"text":"when they are old,"},{"time":411169,"text":"then the level of wealth inequality"},{"time":413542,"text":"should be more or less in line"},{"time":415859,"text":"with the level of income inequality."},{"time":417828,"text":"But it will be very difficult to explain"},{"time":419756,"text":"why you have so much more wealth inequality"},{"time":421950,"text":"than income inequality"},{"time":423434,"text":"with a pure life cycle model,"},{"time":424710,"text":"so you need a story"},{"time":426741,"text":"where people also care"},{"time":428429,"text":"about wealth accumulation for other reasons."},{"time":430960,"text":"So typically, they want to transmit"},{"time":432884,"text":"wealth to the next generation, to their children,"},{"time":436210,"text":"or sometimes they want to accumulate wealth"},{"time":437978,"text":"because of the prestige, the\npower that goes with wealth."},{"time":440746,"text":"So there must be other reasons"},{"time":442130,"text":"for accumulating wealth than just life cycle"},{"time":444120,"text":"to explain what we see in the data."},{"time":446888,"text":"Now, in a large class of dynamic models"},{"time":450234,"text":"of wealth accumulation"},{"time":452210,"text":"with such dynastic motive for accumulating wealth,"},{"time":455768,"text":"you will have all sorts of random,"},{"time":458614,"text":"multiplicative shocks."},{"time":459537,"text":"So for instance, some families"},{"time":461786,"text":"have a very large number of children,"},{"time":463473,"text":"so the wealth will be divided."},{"time":465239,"text":"Some families have fewer children."},{"time":467129,"text":"You also have shocks to rates of return."},{"time":469357,"text":"Some families make huge capital gains."},{"time":471454,"text":"Some made bad investments."},{"time":473249,"text":"So you will always have some mobility"},{"time":475490,"text":"in the wealth process."},{"time":476928,"text":"Some people will move up,\nsome people will move down."},{"time":479303,"text":"The important point is that,"},{"time":480955,"text":"in any such model,"},{"time":481965,"text":"for a given variance of such shocks,"},{"time":484521,"text":"the equilibrium level of wealth inequality"},{"time":486557,"text":"will be a steeply rising function of r minus g."},{"time":491394,"text":"And intuitively, the reason why the difference"},{"time":494263,"text":"between the rate of return to wealth"},{"time":496107,"text":"and the growth rate is important"},{"time":497862,"text":"is that initial wealth inequalities"},{"time":500174,"text":"will be amplified at a faster pace"},{"time":502565,"text":"with a bigger r minus g."},{"time":504634,"text":"So take a simple example,"},{"time":506108,"text":"with r equals five percent and g equals one percent,"},{"time":509874,"text":"wealth holders only need to reinvest"},{"time":511982,"text":"one fifth of their capital income to ensure"},{"time":514621,"text":"that their wealth rises as fast"},{"time":517354,"text":"as the size of the economy."},{"time":519267,"text":"So this makes it easier"},{"time":520650,"text":"to build and perpetuate large fortunes"},{"time":522416,"text":"because you can consume four fifths,"},{"time":524371,"text":"assuming zero tax,"},{"time":526110,"text":"and you can just reinvest one fifth."},{"time":527771,"text":"So of course some families\nwill consume more than that,"},{"time":530359,"text":"some will consume less, so there will be"},{"time":532102,"text":"some mobility in the distribution,"},{"time":533857,"text":"but on average, they only need to reinvest one fifth,"},{"time":536703,"text":"so this allows high wealth inequalities to be sustained."}]},{"cues":[{"time":540472,"text":"Now, you should not be surprised"},{"time":542969,"text":"by the statement that r can be bigger than g forever,"},{"time":546505,"text":"because, in fact, this is what happened"},{"time":548121,"text":"during most of the history of mankind."},{"time":550192,"text":"And this was in a way very obvious to everybody"},{"time":553543,"text":"for a simple reason, which is that growth"},{"time":555321,"text":"was close to zero percent"},{"time":557509,"text":"during most of the history of mankind."},{"time":559130,"text":"Growth was maybe 0.1, 0.2, 0.3 percent,"},{"time":562662,"text":"but very slow growth of population"},{"time":564658,"text":"and output per capita,"},{"time":566655,"text":"whereas the rate of return on capital"},{"time":568539,"text":"of course was not zero percent."},{"time":570395,"text":"It was, for land assets, which was"},{"time":572431,"text":"the traditional form"},{"time":574240,"text":"of assets in preindustrial societies,"},{"time":576641,"text":"it was typically five percent."},{"time":578404,"text":"Any reader of Jane Austen would know that."},{"time":582190,"text":"If you want an annual income of 1,000 pounds,"},{"time":585098,"text":"you should have a capital value"},{"time":586740,"text":"of 20,000 pounds so that"},{"time":588596,"text":"five percent of 20,000 is 1,000."},{"time":591146,"text":"And in a way, this was"},{"time":593163,"text":"the very foundation of society,"},{"time":594941,"text":"because r bigger than g"},{"time":597976,"text":"was what allowed holders of wealth and assets"},{"time":602100,"text":"to live off their capital income"},{"time":604790,"text":"and to do something else in life"},{"time":607490,"text":"than just to care about their own survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":610685,"text":"Now, one important conclusion"},{"time":612845,"text":"of my historical research is that"},{"time":614836,"text":"modern industrial growth did not change"},{"time":617547,"text":"this basic fact as much as one might have expected."},{"time":620371,"text":"Of course, the growth rate"},{"time":622050,"text":"following the Industrial Revolution"},{"time":623858,"text":"rose, typically from zero to one to two percent,"},{"time":628180,"text":"but at the same time, the rate of return"},{"time":630110,"text":"to capital also rose"},{"time":631755,"text":"so that the gap between the two"},{"time":634180,"text":"did not really change."},{"time":635636,"text":"So during the 20th century,"},{"time":637886,"text":"you had a very unique combination of events."},{"time":640530,"text":"First, a very low rate of return"},{"time":642547,"text":"due to the 1914 and 1945 war shocks,"},{"time":645563,"text":"destruction of wealth, inflation,"},{"time":647868,"text":"bankruptcy during the Great Depression,"},{"time":649848,"text":"and all of this reduced"},{"time":651513,"text":"the private rate of return to wealth"},{"time":653263,"text":"to unusually low levels"},{"time":655158,"text":"between 1914 and 1945."},{"time":657497,"text":"And then, in the postwar period,"},{"time":659333,"text":"you had unusually high growth rate,"},{"time":662570,"text":"partly due to the reconstruction."},{"time":664944,"text":"You know, in Germany, in France, in Japan,"},{"time":666869,"text":"you had five percent growth rate"},{"time":668420,"text":"between 1950 and 1980"},{"time":671570,"text":"largely due to reconstruction,"},{"time":673213,"text":"and also due to very large demographic growth,"},{"time":675564,"text":"the Baby Boom Cohort effect."},{"time":677705,"text":"Now, apparently that's not going to last for very long,"},{"time":680143,"text":"or at least the population growth"},{"time":681818,"text":"is supposed to decline in the future,"},{"time":684586,"text":"and the best projections we have is that"},{"time":688242,"text":"the long-run growth is going to be closer"},{"time":690070,"text":"to one to two percent"},{"time":691493,"text":"rather than four to five percent."},{"time":693439,"text":"So if you look at this,"},{"time":696116,"text":"these are the best estimates we have"},{"time":698257,"text":"of world GDP growth"},{"time":699913,"text":"and rate of return on capital,"},{"time":702272,"text":"average rates of return on capital,"},{"time":704360,"text":"so you can see that during most"},{"time":705428,"text":"of the history of mankind,"},{"time":706945,"text":"the growth rate was very small,"},{"time":708558,"text":"much lower than the rate of return,"},{"time":710392,"text":"and then during the 20th century,"},{"time":712754,"text":"it is really the population growth,"},{"time":714925,"text":"very high in the postwar period,"},{"time":717197,"text":"and the reconstruction process"},{"time":718797,"text":"that brought growth"},{"time":720370,"text":"to a smaller gap with the rate of return."},{"time":723441,"text":"Here I use the United Nations population projections,"},{"time":726964,"text":"so of course they are uncertain."},{"time":729440,"text":"It could be that we all start"},{"time":730831,"text":"having a lot of children in the future,"},{"time":732937,"text":"and the growth rates are going to be higher,"},{"time":735702,"text":"but from now on,"},{"time":736951,"text":"these are the best projections we have,"},{"time":739753,"text":"and this will make global growth"},{"time":741687,"text":"decline and the gap between"},{"time":744443,"text":"the rate of return go up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746446,"text":"Now, the other unusual event"},{"time":749308,"text":"during the 20th century"},{"time":750979,"text":"was, as I said,"},{"time":752308,"text":"destruction, taxation of capital,"},{"time":754624,"text":"so this is the pre-tax rate of return."},{"time":757359,"text":"This is the after-tax rate of return,"},{"time":760338,"text":"and after destruction,"},{"time":761904,"text":"and this is what brought"},{"time":763681,"text":"the average rate of return"},{"time":765369,"text":"after tax, after destruction,"},{"time":767158,"text":"below the growth rate during a long time period."},{"time":769578,"text":"But without the destruction,"},{"time":771252,"text":"without the taxation, this \nwould not have happened."},{"time":773727,"text":"So let me say that the balance between"},{"time":776970,"text":"returns on capital and growth"},{"time":779326,"text":"depends on many different factors"},{"time":781188,"text":"that are very difficult to predict:"},{"time":783273,"text":"technology and the development"},{"time":785388,"text":"of capital-intensive techniques."},{"time":787972,"text":"So right now, the most capital-intensive sectors"},{"time":790991,"text":"in the economy are the real estate sector, housing,"},{"time":794367,"text":"the energy sector, but it could be in the future"},{"time":797229,"text":"that we have a lot more robots in a number of sectors"},{"time":800941,"text":"and that this would be a bigger share"},{"time":802830,"text":"of the total capital stock that it is today."},{"time":804740,"text":"Well, we are very far from this,"},{"time":806734,"text":"and from now, what's going on"},{"time":808500,"text":"in the real estate sector, the energy sector,"},{"time":810289,"text":"is much more important for the total capital stock"},{"time":812415,"text":"and capital share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813549,"text":"The other important issue"},{"time":815582,"text":"is that there are scale effects\nin portfolio management,"},{"time":817732,"text":"together with financial complexity,"},{"time":820151,"text":"financial deregulation,"},{"time":821601,"text":"that make it easier to get higher rates of return"},{"time":824310,"text":"for a large portfolio,"},{"time":825937,"text":"and this seems to be particularly strong"},{"time":828600,"text":"for billionaires, large capital endowments."},{"time":830582,"text":"Just to give you one example,"},{"time":832872,"text":"this comes from the Forbes billionaire rankings"},{"time":836205,"text":"over the 1987-2013 period,"},{"time":839535,"text":"and you can see the very top wealth holders"},{"time":842323,"text":"have been going up at six, seven percent per year"},{"time":845440,"text":"in real terms above inflation,"},{"time":847831,"text":"whereas average income in the world,"},{"time":850203,"text":"average wealth in the world,"},{"time":851566,"text":"have increased at only two percent per year."},{"time":854949,"text":"And you find the same"},{"time":856678,"text":"for large university endowments —"},{"time":857954,"text":"the bigger the initial endowments,"},{"time":860222,"text":"the bigger the rate of return."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862290,"text":"Now, what could be done?"},{"time":863968,"text":"The first thing is that I think we need"},{"time":866364,"text":"more financial transparency."},{"time":868479,"text":"We know too little about global wealth dynamics,"},{"time":872320,"text":"so we need international transmission"},{"time":874220,"text":"of bank information."},{"time":875482,"text":"We need a global registry of financial assets,"},{"time":878168,"text":"more coordination on wealth taxation,"},{"time":880659,"text":"and even wealth tax with a small tax rate"},{"time":883771,"text":"will be a way to produce information"},{"time":885987,"text":"so that then we can adapt our policies"},{"time":888669,"text":"to whatever we observe."},{"time":890505,"text":"And to some extent, the fight"},{"time":892343,"text":"against tax havens"},{"time":893824,"text":"and automatic transmission of information"},{"time":895639,"text":"is pushing us in this direction."},{"time":897490,"text":"Now, there are other ways to redistribute wealth,"},{"time":899814,"text":"which it can be tempting to use."},{"time":902771,"text":"Inflation:"},{"time":904127,"text":"it's much easier to print money"},{"time":905826,"text":"than to write a tax code, so that's very tempting,"},{"time":907981,"text":"but sometimes you don't know\nwhat you do with the money."},{"time":910101,"text":"This is a problem."},{"time":911748,"text":"Expropriation is very tempting."},{"time":913611,"text":"Just when you feel some people get too wealthy,"},{"time":915872,"text":"you just expropriate them."},{"time":917166,"text":"But this is not a very efficient way"},{"time":918878,"text":"to organize a regulation of wealth dynamics."},{"time":921711,"text":"So war is an even less efficient way,"},{"time":924190,"text":"so I tend to prefer progressive taxation,"},{"time":926526,"text":"but of course, history — (Laughter) —"},{"time":929100,"text":"history will invent its own best ways,"},{"time":930835,"text":"and it will probably involve"},{"time":932533,"text":"a combination of all of these."}]},{"cues":[{"time":934267,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936133,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":938270,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Thomas Piketty. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943829,"text":"Thomas, I want to ask you two or three questions,"},{"time":945708,"text":"because it's impressive how you're\nin command of your data, of course,"},{"time":949567,"text":"but basically what you suggest is"},{"time":953361,"text":"growing wealth concentration is kind of"},{"time":954934,"text":"a natural tendency of capitalism,"},{"time":956858,"text":"and if we leave it to its own devices,"},{"time":960396,"text":"it may threaten the system itself,"},{"time":962636,"text":"so you're suggesting that we need to act"},{"time":964362,"text":"to implement policies that redistribute wealth,"},{"time":967400,"text":"including the ones we just saw:"},{"time":969121,"text":"progressive taxation, etc."},{"time":970592,"text":"In the current political context,"},{"time":972731,"text":"how realistic are those?"},{"time":974722,"text":"How likely do you think that it is"},{"time":976533,"text":"that they will be implemented?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":978277,"text":"Thomas Piketty: Well, you know, I think"},{"time":979488,"text":"if you look back through time,"},{"time":981269,"text":"the history of income, wealth and taxation"},{"time":983920,"text":"is full of surprise."},{"time":985522,"text":"So I am not terribly impressed"},{"time":988127,"text":"by those who know in advance"},{"time":989695,"text":"what will or will not happen."},{"time":991326,"text":"I think one century ago,"},{"time":993030,"text":"many people would have said"},{"time":994599,"text":"that progressive income taxation would never happen"},{"time":996737,"text":"and then it happened."},{"time":998257,"text":"And even five years ago,"},{"time":1000246,"text":"many people would have said that bank secrecy"},{"time":1002598,"text":"will be with us forever in Switzerland,"},{"time":1004623,"text":"that Switzerland was too powerful"},{"time":1006411,"text":"for the rest of the world,"},{"time":1007900,"text":"and then suddenly it took a few U.S. sanctions"},{"time":1010861,"text":"against Swiss banks for a big change to happen,"},{"time":1013483,"text":"and now we are moving toward"},{"time":1015186,"text":"more financial transparency."},{"time":1016862,"text":"So I think it's not that difficult"},{"time":1021143,"text":"to better coordinate politically."},{"time":1023612,"text":"We are going to have a treaty"},{"time":1025670,"text":"with half of the world GDP around the table"},{"time":1028719,"text":"with the U.S. and the European Union,"},{"time":1030721,"text":"so if half of the world GDP is not enough"},{"time":1032847,"text":"to make progress on financial transparency"},{"time":1035513,"text":"and minimal tax for multinational corporate profits,"},{"time":1039597,"text":"what does it take?"},{"time":1041261,"text":"So I think these are not technical difficulties."},{"time":1044884,"text":"I think we can make progress"},{"time":1046808,"text":"if we have a more pragmatic\napproach to these questions"},{"time":1049395,"text":"and we have the proper sanctions"},{"time":1051296,"text":"on those who benefit from financial opacity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054287,"text":"BG: One of the arguments"},{"time":1055940,"text":"against your point of view"},{"time":1057373,"text":"is that economic inequality"},{"time":1058815,"text":"is not only a feature of capitalism\nbut is actually one of its engines."},{"time":1062452,"text":"So we take measures to lower inequality,"},{"time":1065253,"text":"and at the same time we lower growth, potentially."},{"time":1067660,"text":"What do you answer to that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1069220,"text":"TP: Yeah, I think inequality"},{"time":1070949,"text":"is not a problem per se."},{"time":1072838,"text":"I think inequality up to a point"},{"time":1074878,"text":"can actually be useful for innovation and growth."},{"time":1077530,"text":"The problem is, it's a question of degree."},{"time":1079723,"text":"When inequality gets too extreme,"},{"time":1082267,"text":"then it becomes useless for growth"},{"time":1085156,"text":"and it can even become bad"},{"time":1086618,"text":"because it tends to lead to high perpetuation"},{"time":1089675,"text":"of inequality over time"},{"time":1091311,"text":"and low mobility."},{"time":1093177,"text":"And for instance, the kind of wealth concentrations"},{"time":1096463,"text":"that we had in the 19th century"},{"time":1099340,"text":"and pretty much until World War I"},{"time":1101265,"text":"in every European country"},{"time":1103030,"text":"was, I think, not useful for growth."},{"time":1105124,"text":"This was destroyed by a combination"},{"time":1107226,"text":"of tragic events and policy changes,"},{"time":1109567,"text":"and this did not prevent growth from happening."},{"time":1111839,"text":"And also, extreme inequality can be bad"},{"time":1115282,"text":"for our democratic institutions"},{"time":1117480,"text":"if it creates very unequal access to political voice,"},{"time":1119863,"text":"and the influence of private money"},{"time":1121728,"text":"in U.S. politics, I think,"},{"time":1123730,"text":"is a matter of concern right now."},{"time":1126270,"text":"So we don't want to return to that kind of extreme,"},{"time":1129346,"text":"pre-World War I inequality."},{"time":1131436,"text":"Having a decent share of the national wealth"},{"time":1135110,"text":"for the middle class is not bad for growth."},{"time":1138500,"text":"It is actually useful"},{"time":1139781,"text":"both for equity and efficiency reasons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1142865,"text":"BG: I said at the beginning"},{"time":1144530,"text":"that your book has been criticized."},{"time":1146639,"text":"Some of your data has been criticized."},{"time":1147880,"text":"Some of your choice of data sets has been criticized."},{"time":1150346,"text":"You have been accused of cherry-picking data"},{"time":1152222,"text":"to make your case. What do you answer to that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1154959,"text":"TP: Well, I answer that I am very happy"},{"time":1156886,"text":"that this book is stimulating debate."},{"time":1159353,"text":"This is part of what it is intended for."},{"time":1161834,"text":"Look, the reason why I put all the data online"},{"time":1165128,"text":"with all of the detailed computation"},{"time":1166974,"text":"is so that we can have \nan open and transparent"},{"time":1169308,"text":"debate about this."},{"time":1170977,"text":"So I have responded point by point"},{"time":1172743,"text":"to every concern."},{"time":1174535,"text":"Let me say that if I was to rewrite the book today,"},{"time":1177648,"text":"I would actually conclude"},{"time":1179189,"text":"that the rise in wealth inequality,"},{"time":1181383,"text":"particularly in the United States,"},{"time":1183310,"text":"has been actually higher\nthan what I report in my book."},{"time":1185683,"text":"There is a recent study by Saez and Zucman"},{"time":1188928,"text":"showing, with new data"},{"time":1190520,"text":"which I didn't have at the time of the book,"},{"time":1192297,"text":"that wealth concentration in the U.S. has risen"},{"time":1194824,"text":"even more than what I report."},{"time":1196760,"text":"And there will be other data in the future."},{"time":1198791,"text":"Some of it will go in different directions."},{"time":1200942,"text":"Look, we put online almost every week"},{"time":1205041,"text":"new, updated series on the\nWorld Top Income Database"},{"time":1207975,"text":"and we will keep doing so in the future,"},{"time":1209875,"text":"in particular in emerging countries,"},{"time":1212181,"text":"and I welcome all of those who want to contribute"},{"time":1215110,"text":"to this data collection process."},{"time":1217456,"text":"In fact, I certainly agree"},{"time":1220264,"text":"that there is not enough"},{"time":1221878,"text":"transparency about wealth dynamics,"},{"time":1223756,"text":"and a good way to have better data"},{"time":1225671,"text":"would be to have a wealth tax"},{"time":1227536,"text":"with a small tax rate to begin with"},{"time":1229107,"text":"so that we can all agree"},{"time":1231446,"text":"about this important evolution"},{"time":1233010,"text":"and adapt our policies to whatever we observe."},{"time":1236337,"text":"So taxation is a source of knowledge,"},{"time":1238399,"text":"and that's what we need the most right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1241335,"text":"BG: Thomas Piketty, merci beaucoup."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1243150,"text":"Thank you.\nTP: Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}